    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Chiovendaea eriantha are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antifungal, antibacterial, and antidiabetic properties. The anti-inflammatory property of Chiovendaea eriantha is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antioxidant property of this plant is due to the presence of phenolic compounds, which can scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The antifungal and antibacterial properties of Chiovendaea eriantha are attributed to the presence of volatile oils and terpenoids, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of fungi and bacteria by disrupting their cell membranes. The antidiabetic property of this plant is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which have been shown to increase insulin sensitivity and glucose uptake in cells.",
