    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Chiovendaea eriantha are infusion, tea, tincture, salve, and decoction. Infusion involves steeping dried leaves in hot water to create a tea-like beverage, which is used to treat various ailments due to its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Decoction is a more robust preparation, where the plant material is boiled in water to extract its active compounds, often used for digestive issues. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant, typically made with ethanol or glycerin, used to treat fever, pain, and respiratory problems. Salve is a topical preparation, made by infusing the plant in oil or fat, used to treat skin conditions and wounds due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects.",
